      <p>
        <strong>Lossy formats</strong> achieve smaller file sizes by permanently removing audio data that (theoretically) humans can't perceive. Once removed, this data is gone forever‚Äîyou can't "restore" an MP3 to CD quality.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Lossless formats</strong> compress audio without removing any data. Like a ZIP file for audio. When decompressed, you get back the exact original.
      </p>

      <h3 id="bitrate-guide" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">The Bitrate Guide</h3>

